-- West Ham Manager Allardyce Signs Two-Year Contract, Gold Says
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-11T15:48:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-11/west-ham-manager-allardyce-signs-two-year-contract-gold-says.html
West Ham manager Sam Allardyce signed
a new two-year contract with the Premier League soccer team,
club co-owner David Gold said on Twitter.  Allardyce, 58, is in his second season at West Ham after
leading the team back to the Premier League last year by winning
the playoffs in the second-tier Championship. The Hammers are
10th in the 20-team league with two matches remaining.  “I am delighted to announce that our manager Sam Allardyce
has signed a new two-year contract,” Gold said on Twitter.  Allardyce has previously coached Bolton, Newcastle and
Blackburn in the Premier League.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
